                        <provenance type="found">Macalister (1945, 53), states that <q>Nothing is recorded of the history of the stone, except the statement in the [National] Museum Register, that the fragments came from the neighbourhood of Baltinglass</q>. Brash (1879, 324), however, gives the 'neighbourhood of Donard' as the find location but without further details. Gippert (2001, 49) records that the second fragment could not be found in the National Museum in 1988. David Jackson, Technical Assistant on the Ogham in 3D project, discovered the second fragment in March 2011, lying quite close to the first and exhibiting the same markings, probably made by a modern drill.
